# Build context filter for the images built from the REPOSITORY ROOT: the Go
# backend (which needs packages/config/connectors.yaml, outside its module) and
# the Next.js web app (which needs the workspace lockfile and packages/contracts).
# services/ml builds from its own directory and has its own .dockerignore.
#
# Without this file the root context ships node_modules, the git history, an
# unrelated product, and — worst — the development JWT signing key. A build
# context is not private: every file in it is uploaded to the daemon and any of
# them can be COPYd into a layer by a later edit to a Dockerfile.
#
# This is a denylist rather than an allowlist on purpose. An allowlist that is
# subtly wrong omits a source file and fails the build loudly, which is fine —
# but one that is subtly right for today omits a file added tomorrow. The
# categories below are stable; the source tree is not.

# --- Secrets. These must never enter a build context, for any image. ---
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/.env
**/.env.*
deploy/dev-secrets/
deploy/secrets/

# --- Version control, CI, and agent tooling. ---
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/
.claude/
.cursor/

# --- Dependencies. Restored inside the image from the lockfile. ---
**/node_modules/
**/.pnpm-store/

# --- Build outputs. Rebuilt inside the image; a stale one can shadow the fresh
#     build, which is how a fixed bug survives a deploy. ---
**/.next/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/out/
**/*.egg-info/
**/__pycache__/
**/.venv/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/coverage/

# --- Products and docs that no image needs. apps/pallet-ross is an unrelated
#     product (already excluded from the pnpm workspace); apps/mobile is not
#     built here; graphify-out is a generated knowledge graph. ---
apps/pallet-ross/
apps/mobile/
graphify-out/
product/
**/*.md
!packages/**/*.md

# --- Local noise. ---
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
docker-compose.override.yml
